      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That's a risky idea to take on your own, as warfarin requires careful monitoring to prevent dangerous bleeding or clotting events. You should never adjust your dosage without consulting your doctor, who can check your INR levels to ensure your blood is within the safe therapeutic range. Please call your healthcare provider immediately to discuss any changes in your regimen before making any adjustments to your medication.",
